The paper presents a heuristic optimization technique for solving personnel scheduling problems, which is a common topic in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The technique involves evolutionary algorithms, which are a popular subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the effectiveness and execution speed of the technique, which are important considerations in robotics and control systems (cs.RO). The technique involves iterative improvement and constructive repair, which are common themes in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses experimental results on two different domains of personnel scheduling, which is a common topic in software engineering (cs.SE).
